sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant C as Caller
  participant E as Workflow Engine
  participant K as Lock (ADR-022)
  participant S as Storage (ADR-021)
  participant Q as Scheduler (ADR-020)
  participant B as Event Backbone (ADR-016)

  Note over C,E: signal(workflowId, event)
  C->>E: signal()
  E->>E: serialize per-workflow (in-process chain)
  E->>K: tryAcquire(workflow/workflowId, engineId)
  K-->>E: held (guards concurrent modification)
  E->>S: get(instance)
  S-->>E: instance model
  E->>E: find transition · run guard · run action (from definition)
  E->>S: put(next instance state)
  E->>Q: cancel(old timeout) + scheduleAfter(new state timeout)
  E->>B: publish WorkflowTransitioned
  alt target is terminal
    E->>S: put(completed/failed)
    E->>Q: cancel(timeout)
    E->>B: publish WorkflowCompleted / WorkflowFailed
  end
  E->>K: release(workflow/workflowId)
  E-->>C: updated instance model

  Note over Q,E: later — timeout fires
  Q->>E: handler → _onTimeout(workflowId, state, version)
  E->>K: tryAcquire → get → (state+version still match?) → transition to onTimeout.to
  E->>B: publish WorkflowTimedOut (+ Completed/Failed if terminal)
